# ── Stencil environment (example) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Reference for the environment variables Stencil honours.
#
# NOTE: the stencil binary has no dotenv loader — it reads REAL environment
# variables, not this file. Apply these with `export VAR=value` in your shell
# (or in ~/.zshrc to persist), or pass the equivalent CLI flag. A bare `.env`
# is NOT read automatically.

# Where the learning store is written and read:
#   <dir>/learned.json     — allow/deny tally consulted by `detect --censor`
#   <dir>/decisions.jsonl  — append-only decision log (the future ML training set)
#
# ⚠  decisions.jsonl contains REAL sensitive values. Point this at a private
#    location and never let it get committed — keep it outside any repo, or
#    git-ignore the folder.
#
# Precedence: `--data-dir <dir>` flag  >  STENCIL_DATA_DIR  >  default
# Default when unset: $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/stencil, else ~/.config/stencil
# Use an absolute path — Stencil does not expand `~`.
STENCIL_DATA_DIR=/absolute/path/to/visible/folder
